The paper focuses on analyzing heterogeneous information networks and proposes a framework for ranking objects and meta paths. This falls under the scope of information retrieval (IR) and data mining (DB) which are covered by cs.IR and cs.DB respectively. The use of random walk processes and tensor analysis suggests a focus on machine learning (LG) and artificial intelligence (AI) which are covered by cs.LG and cs.AI respectively. Finally, the paper also discusses the use of meta paths to capture rich semantics, which is a topic covered by social and information networks (SI) which is covered by cs.SI.
